    <weatherForecast/>
    <avalancheActivity>
      <highlights>At elevated altitudes the avalanche prone locations are more prevalent.</highlights>
      <comment>The fresh wind slabs can still be released in some cases in particular on near-ridge shady slopes and generally at elevated altitudes. This applies in particular in case of a large load. Medium-sized avalanches are possible. Avalanches can in very isolated cases be triggered in the old snowpack and reach large size. &lt;br/> &lt;br/> In all aspects hardly any more gliding avalanches and moist snow slides are possible as the temperature drops.</comment>
    </avalancheActivity>
    <snowpackStructure>
